<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang='en'>
<head>
  <meta charset='UTF-8' />
  <title></title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no" />

<style>

  /**
   * Base
   */

  body {
    padding: 46mm 0 0 0;

    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  div { margin: 0; padding: 0; }


  /**
   * Doc Info
   */

  .sponsors {
    position: absolute;
    top: 145px;
    left: 110px;

    width: 60%;
  }

  .sponsors .sponsors-content {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;

    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;

    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .date {
    position: absolute;
    top: 130px;
    right: 0;

    width: 20%;
  }


  /**
   * Main
   */

  .main p {
    text-indent: 30px;
    text-align: justify;

    margin-bottom: 18px;

    page-break-inside: avoid;
  }

  .main p:first-child {
    text-indent: 90px;
  }

  .main p:first-child .clause {
    display: none;
  }

  .main .clause {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-style: oblique;
  }

  
  /**
   * Signatures
   */

  .signatures {
    width: 50%;

    padding-left: 50%;
    margin-right: 0;
    padding-right: 0;
    padding-top: 80px;
  }

  .signatures .signature {
    width: 100%;

    border-top: 1px solid black;

    padding-bottom: 80px;

    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
</style>

</head>
<body>
  <div class="sponsors">
    <p class="sponsors-content">
      Aldermen
      Carrie M. Austin,
      Roberto Maldonado,
      Anthony Napolitano,
      Ameya Pawar,
      and City Clerk Susana A. Mendoza
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="date">
    July 20, 2016
  </div>

  <div class="main">
    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      Envision Chicago is a new initiative for students in Chicago Public High
      Schools to share ideas to improve city laws through a scholarship contest;
      and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      Envision Chicago gives CPS students the chance to imagine a better Chicago
      and make suggestions on how to improve their neighborhoods, wards, and
      schools; and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      Envision Chicago introduces students to the laws of Chicago through
      ChicagoCode.org, the city's first open data edition of it's municipal code
      created through a partnership between the Chicago City Clerk's Office and
      The OpenGov Foundation; and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      Envision Chicago allows students to participate in the legislative process
      in a way that speaks to them most effectively, through technology; and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      Diana Bustamente of Lakeview High School, Gabriela Casarrubias of Marine
      Leadership Academy, Lavon Halloway of Excel Academy, and Victor Story of
      William Howard Taft High School all demonstrated a passion for civic
      engagement; and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      One student from each of the four schools was awarded a $1,000 scholarship
      so that they may build upon their education; and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      Microsoft, Haymarket, ComEd, Comcast, and The Smart Chicago Collaborative
      generously invested in the future of our city's youth by funding
      scholarships for Envision Chicago; and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-whereas">Whereas</span>,
      Encouraging civic engagement by our youth is one of the most important steps
      our city can take to make Chicago the best city it can be; now, therefore,
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-resolved">Be it resolved</span>,
      The we, the Mayor and Members of the City Council of the City of Chicago,
      assembled this twentieth day of July, 2016, do hereby congratulate Diana
      Bustamenta, Gabriela Casarrubias, Lavon Halloway, and Victor Story on being
      the winners of Envision Chicago in its inaugural year; and
    </p>

    <p>
      <span class="clause clause-resolved">Be it further resolved</span>,
      That suitable copies of this resolution are presented to each student as a
      token of our appreciation and esteem.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="signatures">
    <div class="signature">
      <p>Mayor</p>
    </div>
    <div class="signature">
      <p>City Clerk</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
